description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you strive to deliver outstanding care to patients in our community?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Can you demonstrate a commitment to compassionate, person-centred care?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If the answer is yes, then we are looking for you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking Integrated Support Workers to join our Crisis Response Service across East Sussex on a 6 month Fixed Term Contract.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for flexible, motivated and enthusiastic individuals who are willing to learn new skills. If you would like to support us to prevent avoidable hospital admissions, and have a passion for delivering outstanding care in your local community, then please apply to join our multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidates will support people to wash and dress independently, and motivate them to regain their independence with activities of daily living, under the supervision of an Integrated Senior Support Worker or Registered Practitioner.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidates will work to an internal rotation off-duty between the hours of 8am and 10pm, which will include weekends. Independent travel between patient&#39;s homes and the office base in a timely manner is required; access to a vehicle insured for business use is essential.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In return we will reward you with a full induction and training programme as well as an excellent benefits package.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMagda BarkerJob titleService ManagerEmail addressmagda.barker@nhs.netTelephone number07974 191301&lt;/p&gt;
